
Overview of verb droop

The verb droop has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) sag, droop, swag, flag -- (droop, sink, or settle from or as if from pressure or loss of tautness)
2. droop, loll -- (hang loosely or laxly; "His tongue lolled")
3. wilt, droop -- (become limp; "The flowers wilted")

Overview of adj drooping

The adj drooping has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. drooping, flagging -- (weak from exhaustion)
2. drooping, droopy, sagging -- (hanging down (as from exhaustion or weakness))
3. cernuous, drooping, nodding, pendulous, weeping -- (having branches or flower heads that bend downward; "nodding daffodils"; "the pendulous branches of a weeping willow"; "lilacs with drooping panicles of fragrant flowers")
